ns1:grid-level a skos:ConceptScheme ;
    rdfs:comment "The permit register carries a grid reference at THREE levels - the discharge SITE (DISCHARGE_NGR), the OUTLET (OUTLET_GRID_REF) and the EFFLUENT (EFFLUENT_GRID_REF). A discharge point here is keyed at the finest level but the store's DEFAULT geometry is the coarsest, because the site reference is what the public register surfaces as -the- discharge location. All three are published, each tagged with the level it came from, so a consumer can choose - and so that a query never silently fans out across geometries that mean different things." ;
    skos:prefLabel "Which register column a discharge point's grid reference came from" .

